records.addlTxt:
Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.

AS TO COUNT 1:

Court sentences defendant to serve 6 days in the House of Correction consecutive to any other sentence with credit for 6 (six) days, a TIME SERVED DISPOSITION.

  
Court ordered defendant pay all mandatory costs, fees and surcharges by December 7, 2016 or entry of a civil judgment shall be imposed. 

Court ordered DNA sample after today's proceedings. Court ordered January 20, 2016 at 9:00 a.m. jury trial vacated. 

-20 day appeal given,
 
Filed;
-Pretrial Incarceration Credit.

Defendant Maranda N Webber in court with attorney Matthew Adrian Lamke.  Kelly O'Neill appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk: TC. Case calendared for final pre-trial.

AS TO COUNT 1:

Defendant changes plea to GUILTY. Defendant examined as to his plea, advised of his Constitutional rights and the maximum penalty. Court found that defendant freely, voluntarily and intelligently waived his rights. Plea questionnaire received and filed. Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea. Court found defendant guilty as charged in the criminal complaint and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record. Defendant further advised that if she is not a US citizen deportation is possible.

Defendant Maranda N Webber in court with attorney Matthew Adrian Lamke.  Kelly O'Neill appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk: KAR.  Case calendared for plea hearing.
For reasons stated on the record, Court ordered case adjourned for Final Pretrial Conference and Jury Trial in Branch 37.  Final pre-trial scheduled for December 7, 2015 at 01:30 pm.  Jury trial scheduled for January 20, 2016 at 09:00 am.

Defendant Maranda N Webber in court.  Brittany Skye Kachingwe appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk: TC. Case calendared for projected guilty plea. Attorney Matthew Lamke is unavailable for today's proceedings.   Court ordered case adjourned for projected guilty plea in Branch 37.   Agreed Upon Request for a New Court Date is signed and filed.  Plea hearing scheduled for September 28, 2015 at 01:30 pm.

Defendant Maranda N Webber in court with attorney Matthew Adrian Lamke.  Alex T. Mueller appeared for the State of Wisconsin.   Deputy Court Clerk: TC. Case calendared for projected guilty plea and sentencing.   Court ordered case adjourned for projected guilty plea in Branch 37.   Agreed Upon Request for a New Court Date is signed and filed.  Plea hearing scheduled for August 24, 2015 at 08:30 am.

Defendant Maranda N Webber in court with attorney Matthew Adrian Lamke.  Alex T. Mueller appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk: TC.   Defense counsel has received discovery and offer. Court ordered case adjourned for projected guilty plea and sentencing in Branch 37.  Agreed Upon Request for a New Court Date is signed and filed.  Plea/sentencing hearing scheduled for July 7, 2015 at 01:30 pm.

The Court ordered No use or possession of controlled substances without a valid prescription, no drug paraphernalia.  Defendant advised it is a requirement to attend all future court proceedings.  Failure to comply with conditions of bail may result in an additional charge of bail jumping.

Defendant is advised this case is assigned to Judge Dee, Branch 37.  Court reviewed the complaint and found probable cause.  Defendant advised of right to counsel and complaint given to defendant's attorney.  Defendant plead not guilty.  DEFENDANT IS INDIGENT AND QUALIFIES FOR PUBLIC DEFENDER REPRESENTATION.

Defendant Maranda N Webber in court with attorney Christian Thomas Eichenlaub.  Defendant Maranda N Webber in custody.  Carole Manchester appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy court clerk cmt.
  Request for Substitution of Judge received and filed.  Court consented to substitution against Judge Siefert.  Parties are advised the Clerk of Circuit Court reassigned case pursuant to current court rules to Judge Dee, Br. 37.  Pre-trial conference scheduled for June 1, 2015 at 01:30 pm.
